<br>
Like lets say at this years e3 EQ2 is announced.  They wont kill EQ on EQ2s launch date.  Both games will continue on.  Those that like Original EQ can stay, those that want to go to the sequel will too.<br>
<br>
When a company makes a new game, they are, to some extent, competing with themselves, but its a cost of doing business.  EQ1 took about 4-5 years of development.  Im sure as soon as it was finished (or launched), they began plans for EQ2 so they could keep up with all of the people that saw how profitable EQ was and tried to issue a release.<br>
<br>
Many of these games have already been released with development cycles as little as 2 years.  Asherons Call, Anarchy Online, Dark Ages of Camelot....more are down the pike...Shadowbane, Horizons, ect.<br>
<br>
Thus making EQ 2 isnt totally competing with themselves, since other companies would be taking customers away.  Think of EQ 2 as a way to keep existing customers using thier &quot;service&quot; and attracting new ones.<br>
<br>
Make no bones about it, MMORPGs are NOT the same as a video game market.  They are more like a service industry or ISP.  The only way to keep customers is to constantly improve and provide a better product.<br>
<br>
<br>
So, i think it is safe to assume that we will see quite a few more EQ1 expansions....even after the release of EQ2. <p><B><I><FONT color = "white"> Lytic Irontail</B></I><BR>Grandmaster of the Swifttail Caste</FONT><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uertaisi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ertaisi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 11:21:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22881.topic&index=249>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible new EQ expansion in the works?</span><hr size=1> I disagree that they'll focus on the prequel and the sequel at the same time (IF/WHEN it is ever made).  Look at Diablo. The first game all but died when the second was released. <p><a href="http://www.tuathadedanann.net" target="_blank">
