<br>
There will be a day when new players can't stomach the old graphics any longer. (Try playing Ultima IV if you can't understand this. You will also play the best game ever at the same time.) <br>
<br>
The game system has some fundamental problems, and they seriously miscalculated exactly how much time people are willing to spend on their product. When you make a MMORPG you gotta take into account that there will be people who will average 12+ hours per day for four years playing your game. And there will be a few of them. Hordes will average 8 hours every day for year after year. Upper end is reached far too fast. Basically you should always be forced into the same bind that mid 50s are - Raid for better gear or grind for exp? Both makes you better, which makes you most uber now? But this is all tangential.<br>
<br>
They cannot recode EQ enough to compete forever. And it takes 3-5 years to put a MMORPG into the market, even with prior experience. Say 5 years if they want to be able to compete with the current EQ.<br>
<br>
AT THE VERY LATEST they started working on EQ 2 two years ago. Maybe not a big team at first...<br>
<br>
You can compete with yourself, especially when you are convinced that you will make even more money by doing so. (Look at microsoft, it's not like they got anyone to compete with for real.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxillmonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xillmonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 11:45:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22881.topic&index=251>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible new EQ expansion in the works?</span><hr size=1> If an EQ2 is released I'm pretty shure that EQ would be forgotten. Unless they find a way to intergrate the two. After all the time spent getting to lvl 60 would you really be that eager to start over? Although i must admit, comeing from a person that has only been playing for about 8 months, a totaly new start could be refreshing, no more uber twinks, no more lvl 50's farming mobs that you want for exp. It would completely level the playing field. But i think that some form of intergration (outside of story line) would have to be done for it to be sucessful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufuzzyfoot07.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fuzzyfoot07</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 11:50:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22881.topic&index=252>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.katanya.net/EQ/Stabn.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible new EQ expansion in the works?</span><hr size=1> Combin